WEBVTT

00:00:00.020 --> 00:00:05.400


00:00:07.721 --> 00:00:09.481
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

00:00:37.938 --> 00:00:41.318
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

00:00:41.318 --> 00:00:43.938
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

00:00:45.772 --> 00:00:48.105
Shall we wrap up the class here today?

00:00:48.105 --> 00:00:50.772
- Thank you.
- Thank you, professor.

00:01:05.772 --> 00:01:07.497
Officer Lee.

00:01:10.105 --> 00:01:12.238
Aren't you a little too old

00:01:13.238 --> 00:01:15.272
to take my class?

00:01:15.272 --> 00:01:17.472
'Officer Lee.'

00:01:17.472 --> 00:01:19.572
Hearing you call me that

00:01:19.572 --> 00:01:23.205
makes me feel young again, Detective Kang.

00:01:23.205 --> 00:01:27.805
Sorry, shouldn't have called you that.
You've been Chief Inspector for a while.

00:01:27.805 --> 00:01:30.505
The Kangseng Serial Murder Case.

00:01:32.072 --> 00:01:34.272
The real culprit has been caught.

00:01:36.538 --> 00:01:38.705
It's been 30 years.

00:01:40.745 --> 00:01:42.905
[Prisoner Info Card
Lee Yong Woo]

00:01:42.905 --> 00:01:46.305
He lived in Kangseng County at the time,

00:01:46.305 --> 00:01:49.372
and later moved to Cheongju.

00:01:49.372 --> 00:01:53.872
He was sentenced to life in 1994
for killing his sister-in-law

00:01:53.872 --> 00:01:56.405
and has been serving his sentence ever since.

00:01:57.772 --> 00:01:59.938
He was in prison?

00:02:00.938 --> 00:02:02.272
That's why...

00:02:02.272 --> 00:02:04.505
We happened to visit

00:02:04.505 --> 00:02:08.572
right after Lee Yong Woo's
parole hearing had ended.

00:02:08.572 --> 00:02:14.105
If we'd been any later, he would've been
released as a model prisoner.

00:02:15.772 --> 00:02:18.205
Just thinking about it gives me chills.

00:02:18.205 --> 00:02:21.438
The problem is, Lee Yong Woo's DNA was found

00:02:21.438 --> 00:02:23.872
in only three cases.

00:02:23.872 --> 00:02:25.321
Therefore,

00:02:25.321 --> 00:02:27.772
we'll need his confession for the rest cases.

00:02:29.072 --> 00:02:31.905
Even though the statute
of limitations passed,

00:02:31.905 --> 00:02:35.105
getting his confession won't be easy.

00:02:37.572 --> 00:02:39.305
Sir.

00:02:39.972 --> 00:02:42.005
Please help us.

00:02:42.005 --> 00:02:45.738
You wanted to catch the culprit
more than anyone.

00:02:58.105 --> 00:03:01.059
[Lee Yong Woo]

00:03:04.538 --> 00:03:06.345
Actually,

00:03:06.345 --> 00:03:09.505
Lee Yong Woo requested it himself.

00:03:09.505 --> 00:03:11.938
He asked for you specifically.

00:03:16.805 --> 00:03:18.505
Me?

00:03:44.809 --> 00:03:48.305
[Female body discovered in Kangseng County]

00:03:48.305 --> 00:03:51.427
[Public frustration grows
as investigation stalls]

00:04:08.505 --> 00:04:10.438
We'll now present the commendations.

00:04:10.438 --> 00:04:12.305
[1988 Awards Ceremony
for Outstanding Police Officers]

00:04:12.305 --> 00:04:14.915
[Episode 1]

00:04:42.772 --> 00:04:44.472
These seats are reserved for the awardees.

00:04:44.472 --> 00:04:46.238
Spectators sit in the back.

00:04:46.238 --> 00:04:48.572
It's empty anyway, so what's the big deal?

00:04:50.005 --> 00:04:54.705
Next, we will present commendations
to Jongno Police officers

00:04:54.705 --> 00:04:56.972
for their assistance
in apprehending an organized crime group.

00:04:56.972 --> 00:04:58.238
Please step forward upon hearing your name.

00:04:58.238 --> 00:05:00.338
Can't you hear me?

00:05:00.338 --> 00:05:03.105
That's not your seat.

00:05:03.105 --> 00:05:05.645
Aren't we both just sitting

00:05:05.645 --> 00:05:07.638
where we shouldn't be?

00:05:08.338 --> 00:05:11.005
Then you shouldn't have let it be taken.

00:05:11.005 --> 00:05:13.438
The one who can't keep it is the fool.

00:05:13.438 --> 00:05:15.938
Right? Now that's more like it.

00:05:15.938 --> 00:05:18.738
Otherwise, there'd be
no point in coming here.

00:05:19.605 --> 00:05:22.005
I came to flip this whole thing over.

00:05:22.005 --> 00:05:23.538
And I might as well make it loud.

00:05:23.538 --> 00:05:25.938
Sergeant Choi Jung Mo.

00:05:25.938 --> 00:05:29.872
Quit the act and get lost.
I'll buy you drinks someday.

00:05:33.972 --> 00:05:35.838
Sergeant Choi Jung Mo.

00:05:36.938 --> 00:05:39.505
I'm arresting you on charges of bribery.

00:05:39.505 --> 00:05:41.472
Are you out of your mind?
Get these off me now.

00:05:41.472 --> 00:05:44.505
You know Kim Dae Pyeong,
Dosan gang's second-in-command, don't you?

00:05:44.505 --> 00:05:46.338
The one who gave you the money.

00:05:46.338 --> 00:05:47.705
I... I don't know anything about it.

00:05:47.705 --> 00:05:48.972
Just take these off first.

00:05:48.972 --> 00:05:50.405
Sergeant Choi Jung Mo.

00:05:50.405 --> 00:05:51.472
- Hey!
- Is Sergeant Choi Jung Mo here?

00:05:51.472 --> 00:05:54.538
Don't you see you're making things
difficult for Chief too?

00:05:54.538 --> 00:05:56.305
You really want to stand there that much?

00:05:56.305 --> 00:05:59.105
Hurry up and take these off me.

00:06:00.338 --> 00:06:02.338
Fine, fine.

00:06:02.338 --> 00:06:05.738
There it is, here.

00:06:13.738 --> 00:06:17.238
The officer he just awarded
turns out to be corrupt.

00:06:17.238 --> 00:06:18.672
Think carefully.

00:06:18.672 --> 00:06:22.038
Which will embarrass Chief more?

00:06:28.521 --> 00:06:30.872
- Darn it.
- Good call.

00:06:33.605 --> 00:06:37.538
That's enough of a scene.
Let's head out peacefully.

00:06:37.538 --> 00:06:40.405
Come on, keep your head up.

00:06:44.438 --> 00:06:49.238
Let's continue with the awards.

00:07:00.572 --> 00:07:04.072
Earlier during the ceremony,
a police officer was unexpectedly arrested.

00:07:04.072 --> 00:07:07.272
Is it true there was a corrupt officer
among the award recipients?

00:07:07.272 --> 00:07:08.638
Did you know and still turn a blind eye?

00:07:08.638 --> 00:07:10.638
Please answer us.

00:07:10.638 --> 00:07:12.705
Was this meant as a warning?

00:07:12.705 --> 00:07:13.938
You've always said

00:07:13.938 --> 00:07:17.905
no amount of achievement
can excuse corruption in public office.

00:07:17.905 --> 00:07:21.705
So did you just
demonstrate that belief in action?

00:07:24.938 --> 00:07:26.038
That is correct.

00:07:26.038 --> 00:07:29.005
Then, was that earlier incident
ordered by you, Chief?

00:07:29.005 --> 00:07:31.972
I believed that rather than covering up
wrongdoing within our own ranks,

00:07:31.972 --> 00:07:34.372
exposing it and asking for forgiveness

00:07:34.372 --> 00:07:38.805
is what makes a police force
worthy of public trust.

00:07:38.805 --> 00:07:40.305
I sincerely apologize

00:07:40.305 --> 00:07:43.272
to the public for the police's involvement

00:07:43.272 --> 00:07:46.121
in this unfortunate incident.

00:07:46.121 --> 00:07:47.738
[Auditorium]

00:07:47.738 --> 00:07:51.805
[No Mercy for Corruption,
A Bold Move by the Police Chief]

00:08:03.705 --> 00:08:05.405
I've come back

00:08:07.072 --> 00:08:08.205
home.

00:08:08.205 --> 00:08:10.472
Darn it.

00:08:14.038 --> 00:08:18.038
[Kangseng]

00:08:20.172 --> 00:08:25.072
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

00:08:31.172 --> 00:08:32.205
Is that him?

00:08:32.205 --> 00:08:33.372
The most handsome guy in Kangseng?

00:08:33.372 --> 00:08:35.238
Yeah, they say he looks like Andy Lau.

00:08:35.238 --> 00:08:36.405
No way!

00:08:36.405 --> 00:08:37.738
There's an Andy Lau in Kangseng?

00:08:37.738 --> 00:08:40.138
I'm telling you!

00:08:41.638 --> 00:08:43.738
- Oh, come on!
- Just a middle-aged guy.

00:08:43.738 --> 00:08:45.472
What a waste of time.

00:08:45.472 --> 00:08:46.472
More like Sammo Hung.

00:08:46.472 --> 00:08:48.305
Hey, come on. What is this really?

00:08:48.305 --> 00:08:49.705
- Seriously?
- What's going on?

00:08:49.705 --> 00:08:51.605
Come on, Andy Lau? Give me a break.

00:08:51.605 --> 00:08:54.238
Who started that rumor that he's handsome?

00:08:58.038 --> 00:09:00.238
Yes, this is Kangseng Bookstore.

00:09:00.238 --> 00:09:03.505
Hey, with a face like that,
I'd pack him lunch every day.

00:09:03.505 --> 00:09:04.538
He just made eye contact with me.

00:09:04.538 --> 00:09:07.072
Ki Hwan.

00:09:07.072 --> 00:09:09.005
- Call for you.
- Okay.

00:09:09.005 --> 00:09:10.665
He's so hot!

00:09:10.665 --> 00:09:13.305
His eyes are like a deer's.

00:09:13.305 --> 00:09:15.005
Hello?

00:09:16.538 --> 00:09:19.338
Oh, Ji Won.

00:09:19.338 --> 00:09:21.905
What? Tae Joo is back?

00:09:21.905 --> 00:09:24.572
Okay, I'll be right there.

00:09:24.572 --> 00:09:26.972
[Handcuffed Corrupt Cop at Awards Ceremony]
While others ran Chief with his head down,

00:09:26.972 --> 00:09:28.572
[Auntie's Restaurant]
we ran you instead.

00:09:28.572 --> 00:09:30.505
Kangseng's own madman, Kang Tae Joo.

00:09:30.505 --> 00:09:34.372
Wow, with that cigarette,
you look just like Chow Yun Fat.

00:09:34.372 --> 00:09:35.805
It's not... not a cigarette.

00:09:35.805 --> 00:09:37.972
Stop right there! You punk!

00:09:40.572 --> 00:09:41.772
Hey!

00:09:41.772 --> 00:09:43.438
Where do you think you're running off to?

00:09:43.438 --> 00:09:45.138
You punk!

00:09:45.138 --> 00:09:46.638
[Auntie's Restaurant]
Stop, you!

00:09:46.638 --> 00:09:49.238
Aren't those Detective Do and Detective Jang?

00:09:51.205 --> 00:09:54.205
- You're not going after him?
- My assignment starts tomorrow.

00:09:54.205 --> 00:09:55.505
So you're just letting him go?

00:09:55.505 --> 00:09:57.938
He's clearly just a small-time crook.

00:09:58.601 --> 00:10:00.672
I've told you, don't hit my head!

00:10:00.672 --> 00:10:02.605
Kang Tae Joo!

00:10:02.605 --> 00:10:05.872
You are so full of yourself now
after living in Seoul.

00:10:05.872 --> 00:10:08.272
Detective, please help me.

00:10:08.272 --> 00:10:10.705
- I really didn't do it.
- Who is he?

00:10:10.705 --> 00:10:12.005
A guy I put behind bars before.

00:10:12.005 --> 00:10:13.838
- Hey, what is it?
- When I got caught by you,

00:10:13.838 --> 00:10:15.405
I didn't feel it was unfair!

00:10:15.405 --> 00:10:16.472
Why? What? Go away!

00:10:16.472 --> 00:10:18.985
You punk!

00:10:20.305 --> 00:10:21.338
Detective.

00:10:21.338 --> 00:10:23.405
Good grief.

00:10:24.072 --> 00:10:25.872
Detective Kang?

00:10:25.872 --> 00:10:28.905
How long has it been? Three years?

00:10:28.905 --> 00:10:30.638
Oh my.

00:10:30.638 --> 00:10:33.372
I heard you got kicked out of Seoul.

00:10:33.372 --> 00:10:38.172
You left like you'd never return.
Look at you now.

00:10:41.238 --> 00:10:42.672
I'm innocent!

00:10:42.672 --> 00:10:44.172
I really didn't do anything!

00:10:44.172 --> 00:10:46.838
Alright, let's go.

00:10:46.838 --> 00:10:49.072
Detective.

00:10:49.072 --> 00:10:50.805
We'll talk tomorrow.

00:10:50.805 --> 00:10:53.838
I'm telling you, I didn't do anything!

00:10:53.838 --> 00:10:57.372
- You!
- It's not me!

00:11:01.105 --> 00:11:02.473
You...

00:11:02.473 --> 00:11:04.405
You got kicked out?

00:11:05.105 --> 00:11:06.838
Why?

00:11:07.672 --> 00:11:10.172
[Handcuffed Corrupt Cop at Awards Ceremony]
Move it. Look, is this what it's about?

00:11:10.172 --> 00:11:11.538
Smoking in front of the Chief?

00:11:11.538 --> 00:11:13.505
I told you, it wasn't a cigarette!

00:11:13.505 --> 00:11:15.505
Then what was it?

00:11:21.572 --> 00:11:24.672
I locked up a guy
who took bribes from gangsters.

00:11:24.672 --> 00:11:27.605
Turns out he's
the Police Commissioner's nephew.

00:11:27.605 --> 00:11:29.672
So I got transferred out of nowhere.

00:11:29.672 --> 00:11:32.938
This is ridiculous. Isn't that retaliation?

00:11:34.572 --> 00:11:38.172
Hey, Tae Joo, are you really okay?

00:11:38.172 --> 00:11:39.705
Why wouldn't I be?

00:11:39.705 --> 00:11:41.472
Seriously, it was huge.

00:11:41.472 --> 00:11:42.805
We sold so much today.

00:11:42.805 --> 00:11:45.372
Oh? Tae Joo.

00:11:45.372 --> 00:11:48.672
Hey, it's been a while, guys.

00:11:48.672 --> 00:11:50.905
You're a newlywed,
so you should head home early.

00:11:50.905 --> 00:11:53.705
I'm out for the first time in a while.

00:11:53.705 --> 00:11:55.738
Tae Joo, it's really been ages.

00:11:55.738 --> 00:11:58.372
Right, Un Hui,
I heard you're working under Ji Won.

00:11:58.372 --> 00:11:59.738
- Yes.
- Hey.

00:11:59.738 --> 00:12:02.938
We're not in the mood for greetings now,
so if you're here to eat, then eat.

00:12:02.938 --> 00:12:05.572
If you can get inside in three seconds,
I'm paying for your meals.

00:12:06.339 --> 00:12:09.571
Come on, move!

00:12:09.571 --> 00:12:10.729
Sit down!

00:12:13.738 --> 00:12:15.772
What's going on with them?

00:12:15.772 --> 00:12:17.805
Something wrong?

00:12:17.805 --> 00:12:20.872
When Ms. Seo is acting like that,
it's pretty serious.

00:12:20.872 --> 00:12:23.772
Hey, isn't it weird
calling your own sister "Ms. Seo"?

00:12:23.772 --> 00:12:28.405
I called her "Ji Won" at the newsroom
and got hit for it.

00:12:28.405 --> 00:12:29.838
She still hits people?

00:12:29.838 --> 00:12:32.138
Ah, don't even ask.

00:12:32.138 --> 00:12:35.072
Ki Beom, did you get caught or something?

00:12:36.772 --> 00:12:41.038
Come on, if so, he'd be sitting over there.

00:12:41.038 --> 00:12:42.105
Whatever.

00:12:42.105 --> 00:12:43.538
What's he gonna do, kill me?

00:12:43.538 --> 00:12:45.272
Cheers.

00:12:46.405 --> 00:12:48.605
Hey, forget it.

00:12:48.605 --> 00:12:50.538
Let's just go all the way tonight.

00:12:50.538 --> 00:12:52.405
Just don't pass out before sunrise, alright?

00:12:52.405 --> 00:12:54.138
Okay.

00:12:56.201 --> 00:12:58.089
It's not that way.

00:12:59.672 --> 00:13:01.638
Hold on, we're almost there.

00:13:01.638 --> 00:13:02.738
It's Sun Young.

00:13:02.738 --> 00:13:04.805
Hey, pull yourself together.

00:13:04.805 --> 00:13:06.938
- Sun Young!
- Pull yourself together.

00:13:06.938 --> 00:13:08.138
Hey, Sun Young...

00:13:08.138 --> 00:13:09.805
Hey, act sober. Pretend you're fine.

00:13:09.805 --> 00:13:10.838
Sun Young.

00:13:10.838 --> 00:13:13.305
Hold on, you're too heavy.

00:13:13.305 --> 00:13:16.238
Should we lay him down here?

00:13:16.238 --> 00:13:17.238
Oh, my back.

00:13:17.238 --> 00:13:18.838
Sun Young.

00:13:18.838 --> 00:13:20.572
Sun Young.

00:13:26.338 --> 00:13:27.372
Jeez.

00:13:27.372 --> 00:13:30.372
Oh, I'm home.

00:13:31.105 --> 00:13:33.338
The smell...

00:13:35.105 --> 00:13:38.472
It's you, our Sun Young.

00:13:38.472 --> 00:13:39.605
Sun Young is mad.

00:13:39.605 --> 00:13:40.605
How much did you drink?

00:13:40.605 --> 00:13:42.372
My pretty little sister, my...

00:13:42.372 --> 00:13:44.105
Jeez, you idiot,

00:13:44.105 --> 00:13:46.005
lay off the booze a little.

00:13:46.005 --> 00:13:47.772
I'm...

00:13:47.772 --> 00:13:49.972
Seriously, what is this?

00:13:53.805 --> 00:13:55.138
Is he dead?

00:13:55.138 --> 00:13:56.972
Well...

00:14:00.372 --> 00:14:03.372
We didn't see anything, Sun Young.

00:14:03.372 --> 00:14:04.405
We're leaving.

00:14:04.405 --> 00:14:05.805
Ki Hwan, let's go.

00:14:05.805 --> 00:14:07.572
Is he dead?

00:14:07.572 --> 00:14:09.065
Good night.

00:14:09.065 --> 00:14:11.564
- Is he dead?
- Shut up!

00:14:39.105 --> 00:14:43.805
Dead or alive?

00:14:43.805 --> 00:14:47.705
Dead or alive?

00:14:49.205 --> 00:14:51.305
Alive!

00:15:27.172 --> 00:15:33.972
[Period for Reporting and Surrendering Spies]

00:15:33.972 --> 00:15:37.105
[Stop]

00:15:56.838 --> 00:16:00.438
Excuse me, who are you
to sit in someone else's seat?

00:16:04.805 --> 00:16:05.938
It was my seat before.

00:16:05.938 --> 00:16:08.038
Hey, what do you mean 'your seat'?

00:16:08.038 --> 00:16:09.405
This is where the youngest sits now.

00:16:09.405 --> 00:16:11.405
It's not like you were born in that chair.

00:16:11.405 --> 00:16:13.609
Just sit over there. It's empty anyway.

00:16:13.609 --> 00:16:14.638
Ugh, it's...

00:16:14.638 --> 00:16:16.605
It still reeks of your cigarettes.

00:16:16.605 --> 00:16:19.172
It stinks there.

00:16:19.172 --> 00:16:21.872
You've become a real Seoul snob.
You're the only one who smells it?

00:16:21.872 --> 00:16:25.605
This used to be my seat.

00:16:29.472 --> 00:16:30.505
Rookie?

00:16:30.505 --> 00:16:32.305
Yes, I'm Park Dae Ho.

00:16:32.305 --> 00:16:33.605
Okay, rookie.

00:16:33.605 --> 00:16:38.638
I've been in Seoul the whole time.

00:16:38.638 --> 00:16:40.438
Have you been to Seoul?

00:16:40.438 --> 00:16:41.472
- No.
- Oh my.

00:16:41.472 --> 00:16:44.105
Then you have no idea
how bad the air is there.

00:16:44.105 --> 00:16:46.438
Factories, car exhaust...

00:16:46.438 --> 00:16:50.138
I was about to get lung disease,
so I begged to come here.

00:16:50.138 --> 00:16:51.238
Just to survive.

00:16:51.238 --> 00:16:53.105
Really?

00:16:54.138 --> 00:16:55.205
Please stay seated there.

00:16:55.205 --> 00:16:56.938
Hey, you believe him?

00:16:56.938 --> 00:17:01.172
Look at his complexion.
He looks perfectly fine, oh my.

00:17:01.172 --> 00:17:05.505
If you feel wronged,
just take it as saving a life. Okay?

00:17:05.505 --> 00:17:07.272
Lee Seong Jin!

00:17:10.972 --> 00:17:12.805
Lee Seong Jin, you...

00:17:14.938 --> 00:17:16.838
Hey, Lee Seong Jin!

00:17:18.338 --> 00:17:20.038
[Security Interview Room]
You...

00:17:26.705 --> 00:17:28.638
What kind of world is this nowadays?

00:17:28.638 --> 00:17:31.372
Just to get a confession,
you beat him up like that?

00:17:31.372 --> 00:17:32.438
If this were in Seoul,

00:17:32.438 --> 00:17:34.105
it'd be front-page news.

00:17:34.105 --> 00:17:36.438
Hey! You think working in Seoul
makes you special?

00:17:36.438 --> 00:17:37.938
So what, you punk?

00:17:37.938 --> 00:17:41.005
The prosecutor is demanding
we get a confession today, no matter what.

00:17:41.005 --> 00:17:44.805
I've arrested that guy
three times, so I know him.

00:17:44.805 --> 00:17:49.505
If you hit him with solid evidence,
he just stammers and spills everything.

00:17:49.505 --> 00:17:53.338
It's not like he killed anyone.
Why treat some petty crook like that?

00:17:58.272 --> 00:18:00.472
Why? What is it?

00:18:01.372 --> 00:18:03.105
Hey.

00:18:04.938 --> 00:18:07.605
He did kill someone.

00:18:07.605 --> 00:18:09.872
He's a murderer.

00:18:09.872 --> 00:18:11.572
What?

00:18:26.572 --> 00:18:31.738
With the Olympics just a month away,
things are very unsettled.

00:18:31.738 --> 00:18:34.238
Given the situation,
everyone stay careful, understood?

00:18:34.238 --> 00:18:36.272
- Yes.
- Everyone here?

00:18:36.272 --> 00:18:38.005
Yes.

00:18:39.272 --> 00:18:42.005
I heard the suspect in the Im Bok Hee
murder case has been caught.

00:18:43.405 --> 00:18:45.138
As expected of Prosecutor Cha.

00:18:45.138 --> 00:18:47.505
You really know how to get things done.

00:18:47.505 --> 00:18:49.005
I'm flattered.

00:18:49.005 --> 00:18:53.138
If we hadn't solved this case,
I would've lost my job.

00:18:53.138 --> 00:18:55.372
You know we already have
two unsolved cases at the station, right?

00:18:55.372 --> 00:18:58.005
And both are murder cases.

00:18:58.005 --> 00:18:59.838
Sorry, I feel ashamed.

00:19:00.638 --> 00:19:03.138
This is why the first step matters.

00:19:03.138 --> 00:19:06.338
If you're not confident,
why not hand it over to Mr. Cha now?

00:19:06.338 --> 00:19:07.505
No need, sir.

00:19:07.505 --> 00:19:10.805
It's my case, so I'll see it through.

00:19:17.638 --> 00:19:20.472
- Send it to me by tomorrow.
- Yes, sir.

00:19:24.038 --> 00:19:25.738
Mr. Cha!

00:19:25.738 --> 00:19:28.038
- Oh, yes.
- About the suspect.

00:19:28.038 --> 00:19:29.673
How did you find him?

00:19:30.805 --> 00:19:33.805
The method of strangling the victim
with stockings was unusual.

00:19:33.805 --> 00:19:37.172
So I started with offenders
with stocking-related records.

00:19:37.172 --> 00:19:39.672
Turns out one of them lived nearby.

00:19:39.672 --> 00:19:43.772
We also got a witness
who saw him near the scene.

00:19:43.772 --> 00:19:46.038
Isn't that only natural?

00:19:46.038 --> 00:19:49.338
He lives near the crime scene, you said.

00:19:49.338 --> 00:19:53.405
So there's still no direct evidence, right?

00:19:53.405 --> 00:19:54.938
Make sure you check thoroughly.

00:19:54.938 --> 00:19:57.072
Don't end up like me.

00:20:05.238 --> 00:20:07.689
He's tougher than I expected.

00:20:07.689 --> 00:20:09.205
So please allow me a little more time.

00:20:09.205 --> 00:20:11.272
I'll get a confession out of him.

00:20:11.272 --> 00:20:13.972
No direct evidence?

00:20:15.138 --> 00:20:16.172
He's quite the expert.

00:20:16.172 --> 00:20:17.272
Excuse me?

00:20:17.272 --> 00:20:20.505
What do you mean by that?

00:20:20.505 --> 00:20:22.872
Are you sure Lee Seong Jin is the culprit?

00:20:22.872 --> 00:20:24.872
Of course.

00:20:24.872 --> 00:20:27.138
I mean, there's a witness too.

00:20:27.138 --> 00:20:30.505
But that witness didn't
actually see the crime happen.

00:20:30.505 --> 00:20:32.705
He said he just saw him nearby.

00:20:32.705 --> 00:20:34.338
He's local, not from Seoul.

00:20:34.338 --> 00:20:35.905
Does that really count as evidence?

00:20:35.905 --> 00:20:41.072
Well, the blood type at the scene is B,

00:20:41.072 --> 00:20:43.805
and Lee Seong Jin is also type B...

00:20:45.172 --> 00:20:47.405
I'm type B too!

00:20:49.972 --> 00:20:51.638
You're really doing it like amateurs!

00:20:51.638 --> 00:20:53.338
Sorry.

00:20:59.605 --> 00:21:01.129
Lee Seong Jin...

00:21:01.897 --> 00:21:03.772
I need to meet him myself.

00:21:04.772 --> 00:21:08.705
In February last year,
he was fined for stealing stockings.

00:21:08.705 --> 00:21:11.038
[Criminal Record Certificate]

00:21:14.938 --> 00:21:18.005
Served from April to July. What was it for?

00:21:18.005 --> 00:21:20.805
Well, indecent assault.

00:21:20.805 --> 00:21:23.338
He touched a woman's leg
as she was passing by in stockings.

00:21:23.338 --> 00:21:26.205
I told that guy to live a decent life...

00:21:27.305 --> 00:21:30.905
Anyway, so it's just theft
and indecent assault, right?

00:21:30.905 --> 00:21:34.138
Yes, this would be his first murder.

00:21:34.938 --> 00:21:37.172
Who says he killed anyone?

00:21:37.172 --> 00:21:40.172
Don't jump to conclusions.
Nothing's been proven yet.

00:21:40.172 --> 00:21:41.905
Yes, sir.

00:21:42.605 --> 00:21:44.038
Bring me the case files
and crime scene photos

00:21:44.038 --> 00:21:46.172
of that Im Bok Hee murder case.

00:21:46.172 --> 00:21:48.438
Okay, one moment.

00:21:56.713 --> 00:21:57.772
- Jeez.
- I'm...

00:21:57.772 --> 00:21:59.472
I'm sorry.

00:22:01.338 --> 00:22:05.838
Hey, if you just grab everything like that,
how are you going to sort it out later?

00:22:05.838 --> 00:22:07.372
Jeez.

00:22:07.372 --> 00:22:09.072
Sorry.

00:22:21.405 --> 00:22:22.672
Stop right there.

00:22:22.672 --> 00:22:24.009
Huh?

00:22:24.009 --> 00:22:26.272
Why? What's wrong?

00:22:39.605 --> 00:22:41.538
What is this?

00:22:41.538 --> 00:22:43.593
This is...

00:22:43.593 --> 00:22:44.841
Why are the bodies all different?

00:22:44.841 --> 00:22:47.872
These are the murder cases
that have occurred recently.

00:22:47.872 --> 00:22:49.538
Three in total.

00:22:49.538 --> 00:22:51.538
Three?

00:22:51.538 --> 00:22:52.572
And the killer?

00:22:52.572 --> 00:22:54.272
It's still...

00:22:56.938 --> 00:22:58.872
What's wrong?

00:23:01.472 --> 00:23:03.172
These are

00:23:04.338 --> 00:23:06.305
serial murders.

00:23:10.938 --> 00:23:12.638
Lee Seong Jin!

00:23:13.572 --> 00:23:15.838
Lee Seong... Hey, where's Lee Seong Jin?

00:23:15.838 --> 00:23:18.005
Detective Jang and Detective Do...

00:23:18.005 --> 00:23:20.938
- There they are.
- Come over.

00:23:20.938 --> 00:23:22.305
Lee Seong Jin!

00:23:22.305 --> 00:23:24.505
Lee Seong Jin, it wasn't you, right?

00:23:24.505 --> 00:23:25.638
What are you talking about?

00:23:25.638 --> 00:23:27.172
He's not the real killer!

00:23:27.172 --> 00:23:29.405
Hey, you said it yourself
it wasn't you, right?

00:23:29.405 --> 00:23:31.538
No. It was me!

00:23:31.538 --> 00:23:33.472
I did it!

00:23:34.638 --> 00:23:36.138
What's wrong with you?

00:23:36.138 --> 00:23:37.605
Seong Jin.

00:23:37.605 --> 00:23:38.605
Stop it, you punk.

00:23:38.605 --> 00:23:39.738
He already confessed everything.

00:23:39.738 --> 00:23:41.972
- Ji Hwan, lock him up.
- Yes, sir.

00:23:48.805 --> 00:23:50.272
You beat him again, didn't you?

00:23:50.272 --> 00:23:51.772
Is that even a real confession?

00:23:51.772 --> 00:23:53.238
It's not like that, you punk.

00:23:53.238 --> 00:23:55.005
Don't talk back to me like that.

00:23:55.005 --> 00:23:56.738
Don't give me that.

00:23:57.505 --> 00:23:58.872
Tell me straight.

00:23:58.872 --> 00:24:01.105
The prosecutor in charge got it himself.

00:24:01.105 --> 00:24:02.805
The confession.

00:24:05.805 --> 00:24:06.857
[Name: Lee Seong Jin, currently unemployed]

00:24:06.857 --> 00:24:07.945
[I lost my father in childhood
and live with my mother]

00:24:21.572 --> 00:24:24.238
- Mr. Lee Seong Jin.
- Yes.

00:24:24.238 --> 00:24:26.572
Why are you shaking?

00:24:26.572 --> 00:24:29.097
You're a prosecutor, aren't you?

00:24:29.838 --> 00:24:32.372
Prosecutors aren't scary people.

00:24:32.372 --> 00:24:34.819
We're only scary to people
who've committed crimes.

00:24:35.505 --> 00:24:38.305
Mr. Lee, have you done anything wrong?

00:24:42.138 --> 00:24:43.721
So you

00:24:43.721 --> 00:24:45.905
really didn't kill Im Bok Hee?

00:24:45.905 --> 00:24:46.915
I didn't.

00:24:47.972 --> 00:24:51.072
Oh dear, then you were just unlucky.

00:24:51.072 --> 00:24:53.705
You happened to live in that neighborhood.

00:25:03.038 --> 00:25:05.138
Then,

00:25:05.138 --> 00:25:06.985
Mr. Lee,

00:25:06.985 --> 00:25:09.238
can you help me out a bit?

00:25:10.838 --> 00:25:13.238
I really can't figure it out.

00:25:13.238 --> 00:25:18.505
Why did the killer use
stockings to kill someone?

00:25:20.005 --> 00:25:23.438
You have a certain expertise with stockings.

00:25:23.438 --> 00:25:26.172
That's why you ended up under suspicion too.

00:25:28.638 --> 00:25:30.409
Mr. Lee,

00:25:30.409 --> 00:25:31.905
why do you like stockings?

00:25:32.803 --> 00:25:35.072
Well...

00:25:35.072 --> 00:25:38.372
This is...

00:25:40.872 --> 00:25:44.072
At first, they feel soft.

00:25:44.072 --> 00:25:46.305
But if you keep touching them,

00:25:46.305 --> 00:25:49.505
they all become rough.

00:25:49.505 --> 00:25:54.038
That feeling is strangely intense.

00:25:54.038 --> 00:25:55.738
So it was you.

00:25:56.372 --> 00:25:58.072
What?

00:26:02.305 --> 00:26:05.905
I wasn't sure until I came here.

00:26:12.472 --> 00:26:14.772
But your eyes gave it away.

00:26:14.772 --> 00:26:17.505
Those totally fried eyes.

00:26:18.605 --> 00:26:19.738
You killed her, didn't you?

00:26:19.738 --> 00:26:20.872
No, I didn't.

00:26:20.872 --> 00:26:23.072
I didn't kill her.

00:26:23.072 --> 00:26:25.472
Listen carefully.

00:26:25.472 --> 00:26:28.838
This is the first and last chance
I'm giving you.

00:26:30.772 --> 00:26:32.201
Today,

00:26:32.201 --> 00:26:34.772
if you confess here,

00:26:34.772 --> 00:26:37.638
I'll get you out within five years.

00:26:37.638 --> 00:26:38.921
However,

00:26:38.921 --> 00:26:42.872
if you don't confess
before I walk out that door?

00:26:42.872 --> 00:26:45.772
You'll rot in prison forever.

00:26:45.772 --> 00:26:47.572
Got it?

00:26:48.538 --> 00:26:50.738
- What?
- One,

00:26:51.405 --> 00:26:53.272
two,

00:26:53.272 --> 00:26:55.105
three,

00:26:55.105 --> 00:26:57.572
- four.
- No, please, Mr. Cha.

00:26:57.572 --> 00:26:59.072
Sir!

00:26:59.072 --> 00:27:01.105
Please save me.

00:27:01.105 --> 00:27:03.905
I'm all my mother has.

00:27:03.905 --> 00:27:05.505
She's sick right now.

00:27:05.505 --> 00:27:07.038
Oh dear.

00:27:07.038 --> 00:27:10.572
Then if you don't confess,
you won't even get out by her 80th birthday.

00:27:10.572 --> 00:27:12.072
No, please don't.

00:27:12.072 --> 00:27:14.505
- Five,
- Sir!

00:27:14.505 --> 00:27:16.438
- six,
- No, sir.

00:27:16.438 --> 00:27:18.972
- seven...
- Please spare me.

00:27:18.972 --> 00:27:21.938
I'll let you attend your mother's funeral
as the chief mourner.

00:27:21.938 --> 00:27:23.305
So don't worry.

00:27:23.305 --> 00:27:25.672
No need for a false confession.

00:27:25.672 --> 00:27:27.805
Eight.

00:27:27.805 --> 00:27:31.138
Sir, please don't.

00:27:31.138 --> 00:27:34.305
- Nine.
- Sir!

00:27:34.305 --> 00:27:37.105
Sir!

00:27:37.105 --> 00:27:38.838
Ten.

00:27:41.672 --> 00:27:43.438
I...

00:27:43.438 --> 00:27:47.072
I killed her, sir.

00:27:47.072 --> 00:27:53.038
I killed her, sir.

00:27:53.038 --> 00:27:57.105
I'm sorry. I killed her.

00:27:57.105 --> 00:28:01.805
I killed her, sir...

00:28:01.805 --> 00:28:03.972
[Kangseng Police Station]

00:28:03.972 --> 00:28:06.372
Have him write the statement carefully.

00:28:06.372 --> 00:28:08.372
So he won't make mistakes
during the crime scene reenactment.

00:28:08.372 --> 00:28:11.105
Sure, don't worry.

00:28:11.105 --> 00:28:12.805
Sir!

00:28:12.805 --> 00:28:14.972
Sir!

00:28:14.972 --> 00:28:16.705
- I need to talk to you!
- Hey.

00:28:16.705 --> 00:28:17.738
Let's talk, okay?

00:28:17.738 --> 00:28:18.872
What on earth are you doing?

00:28:18.872 --> 00:28:20.605
What do you mean?

00:28:20.605 --> 00:28:22.405
What's going on?

00:28:22.405 --> 00:28:23.638
Is he talking to me?

00:28:23.638 --> 00:28:26.738
Of course not.
You don't need to worry about it.

00:28:26.738 --> 00:28:28.937
He was recently kicked out of Seoul.

00:28:28.937 --> 00:28:31.905
Apparently he had trouble there too.

00:28:32.705 --> 00:28:33.772
Take care on your way home.

00:28:33.772 --> 00:28:35.438
Oh, sir.

00:28:35.438 --> 00:28:38.138
- Hello.
- Yes, good work.

00:28:38.138 --> 00:28:39.372
Please get home safely.

00:28:39.372 --> 00:28:42.072
What's wrong with you, you lunatic?

00:28:42.072 --> 00:28:44.205
Didn't you say
the prosecutor got the confession himself?

00:28:44.205 --> 00:28:45.572
- Hey.
- So I was going to settle things

00:28:45.572 --> 00:28:47.305
- with him!
- Hey, hey!

00:28:47.305 --> 00:28:49.385
Kang Tae Joo!

00:28:49.385 --> 00:28:53.005
- Let's talk in private, okay?
- Kang Tae Joo?

00:28:56.672 --> 00:29:00.438
It is you, Kang Tae Joo!

00:29:03.872 --> 00:29:06.972
Wow, Tae Joo, you've really changed.

00:29:06.972 --> 00:29:09.305
Hey, Tae Joo!

00:29:09.305 --> 00:29:11.938
It's been such a long time.

00:29:15.105 --> 00:29:18.705
Wow, didn't expect to see you here!

00:29:19.738 --> 00:29:22.438
Hey, good to see you.

00:29:23.938 --> 00:29:26.505
So you became a cop?

00:29:44.638 --> 00:29:48.738
Tae Joo.

00:29:51.372 --> 00:29:54.272
Dead or alive?

00:29:54.272 --> 00:29:55.572
[Kang Tae Joo]

00:29:55.572 --> 00:29:58.572
[Cha Si Young]

00:30:40.872 --> 00:30:43.241
Seems you're in a good mood.

00:30:43.241 --> 00:30:47.405
I caught a murderer today.

00:30:47.405 --> 00:30:51.705
Such a tough case. Wasn't it hard?

00:30:51.705 --> 00:30:56.538
Well, I chose this job out of sense of duty.

00:30:59.705 --> 00:31:02.405
My father used to say

00:31:02.405 --> 00:31:06.405
that you are someone with great capacity.

00:31:07.872 --> 00:31:12.305
It's truly an honor that
the Chairman sees me that way.

00:31:12.305 --> 00:31:14.372
I'm really in a good mood today.

00:31:14.372 --> 00:31:17.772
Meeting someone as beautiful as you,
Hee Jin, makes it even better.

00:31:18.505 --> 00:31:20.205
Oh my.

00:31:23.738 --> 00:31:27.972
Actually, I also ran into
an old friend today.

00:31:28.672 --> 00:31:31.172
Someone I was very close with.

00:31:32.505 --> 00:31:34.205
Mr. Heo.

00:31:35.138 --> 00:31:37.161
Kang Tae Joo and Cha Si Young

00:31:37.161 --> 00:31:38.979
were classmates.

00:31:39.638 --> 00:31:40.838
What are you talking about?

00:31:40.838 --> 00:31:43.538
Are Prosecutor Cha Si Young
and Kang Tae Joo classmates?

00:31:45.338 --> 00:31:46.472
- Really?
- Yes.

00:31:46.472 --> 00:31:47.805
We were surprised too.

00:31:47.805 --> 00:31:49.338
They seemed pretty close.

00:31:49.338 --> 00:31:52.805
Really? What a small world!

00:31:52.805 --> 00:31:54.738
So

00:31:54.738 --> 00:31:57.338
did Detective Kang say anything about it?

00:31:57.338 --> 00:31:59.405
Right, what is that supposed to mean?

00:31:59.405 --> 00:32:02.338
Park Dae Ho, do you know anything?

00:32:02.338 --> 00:32:04.238
Well...

00:32:04.238 --> 00:32:06.472
It's nothing.

00:32:06.472 --> 00:32:08.505
I think I misunderstood earlier.

00:32:08.505 --> 00:32:09.838
Don't mind what I said.

00:32:09.838 --> 00:32:11.572
See?

00:32:11.572 --> 00:32:14.005
We've got the suspect's confession,

00:32:14.005 --> 00:32:15.105
and Detective Kang is back.

00:32:15.105 --> 00:32:17.472
How about we grab a drink together?

00:32:17.472 --> 00:32:20.872
Mr. Heo, since we're all here, how about...

00:32:20.872 --> 00:32:22.172
a drink tonight?

00:32:22.172 --> 00:32:24.538
Sounds good! How about gopchang?

00:32:24.538 --> 00:32:27.205
I've got something I need to do.

00:32:27.205 --> 00:32:29.405
Please go ahead without me.

00:32:29.405 --> 00:32:34.205
Come on, we're doing this for you.
How can you bail on us?

00:32:34.205 --> 00:32:36.605
Just pretend I'm there.

00:32:37.772 --> 00:32:39.705
Forget it, forget it.

00:32:39.705 --> 00:32:41.638
Never mind.

00:32:51.105 --> 00:32:56.072
For the first time since you passed,
I've dressed you in hemp mourning clothes.

00:32:56.072 --> 00:33:01.138
[After Laying You Before the Cornfield]
I gave the neighbors some clothes you made.

00:33:01.138 --> 00:33:05.538
I buried you beside the cornfield
and walked back.

00:33:10.638 --> 00:33:12.338
Go now.

00:33:12.338 --> 00:33:13.938
Right now!

00:33:13.938 --> 00:33:15.638
Now.

00:33:32.638 --> 00:33:36.138
I'm sorry.

00:33:36.138 --> 00:33:38.005
I'm sorry.

00:33:40.372 --> 00:33:42.472
I'll pay for this.

00:33:42.472 --> 00:33:45.638
It's fine. You're just a student.

00:33:45.638 --> 00:33:48.072
I'm not some irresponsible kid.

00:33:48.072 --> 00:33:49.772
Please let me pay, okay?

00:33:49.772 --> 00:33:50.972
That's not your money.

00:33:50.972 --> 00:33:53.059
It's your parents'.

00:33:53.838 --> 00:33:56.038
You can have this,

00:33:56.038 --> 00:33:58.872
so just come to our bookstore
when you buy reference books later.

00:34:01.038 --> 00:34:04.605
It's Yu Jeong Rin.

00:34:09.938 --> 00:34:13.605
I just wanted to
order the reference books in advance.

00:34:13.605 --> 00:34:15.305
Yu Jeong Rin?

00:34:16.338 --> 00:34:18.072
I'll write it down.

00:34:46.938 --> 00:34:52.605
October 8, 1986, Choi Min Ja, 30 years old.

00:34:53.305 --> 00:34:56.338
Found with her hands bound
with a wrapping cloth.

00:34:56.338 --> 00:34:57.972
Strangled.

00:34:57.972 --> 00:35:01.205
There are signs of manual
strangulation on the neck.

00:35:02.572 --> 00:35:08.072
June 11, 1987, Hwang Kang Ae, 21 years old.

00:35:08.072 --> 00:35:12.238
Died by strangulation with a scarf.

00:35:12.238 --> 00:35:15.338
April 29, 1988.

00:35:16.072 --> 00:35:18.738
Im Bok Hee, 29 years old.

00:35:19.505 --> 00:35:22.305
Murdered by strangulation with stockings.

00:35:25.205 --> 00:35:30.572
If confirmed as serial murders,
the cases will be consolidated.

00:35:30.572 --> 00:35:35.672
Choi Min Ja and Hwang Kang Ae cases
were handled by Prosecutor Hwang Jae Hoon.

00:35:35.672 --> 00:35:39.205
Im Bok Hee was assigned to Cha Si Young.

00:35:40.105 --> 00:35:42.153
So it'll go

00:35:42.153 --> 00:35:44.205
to one of those two.

00:36:02.638 --> 00:36:03.838
You're still here?

00:36:03.838 --> 00:36:04.838
What are you doing here?

00:36:04.838 --> 00:36:06.538
- You didn't even call.
- What is this?

00:36:06.538 --> 00:36:07.738
- What is it?
- Should've let me know.

00:36:07.738 --> 00:36:10.872
- Hey, hold on.
- Stop.

00:36:10.872 --> 00:36:12.172
- What's wrong?
- Hold on.

00:36:12.172 --> 00:36:13.538
- Let me see.
- Hey.

00:36:13.538 --> 00:36:14.838
Let's go out. Let's go.

00:36:14.838 --> 00:36:16.538
- Hold on.
- Alright, let's go.

00:36:16.538 --> 00:36:17.705
- Seriously.
- Let's go grab a bite.

00:36:17.705 --> 00:36:19.372
Alright, alright.

00:36:19.372 --> 00:36:22.705
Isn't the guy in the bookstore really sweet?

00:36:22.705 --> 00:36:24.938
He'll remember my name, right?

00:36:25.905 --> 00:36:27.672
"It's Yu Jeong Rin."

00:36:27.672 --> 00:36:29.972
Hey!

00:36:29.972 --> 00:36:32.338
That scared me!

00:36:32.338 --> 00:36:34.405
What? It's just a scarecrow.

00:36:34.405 --> 00:36:36.205
You startled me.

00:36:41.638 --> 00:36:43.005
- Min Ji.
- Yes?

00:36:43.005 --> 00:36:44.705
Over there...

00:36:50.705 --> 00:36:52.572
Do you know Prosecutor Hwang Jae Hoon?

00:36:52.572 --> 00:36:53.838
Hwang Jae Hoon?

00:36:53.838 --> 00:36:54.838
Of course.

00:36:54.838 --> 00:36:57.772
Until recently, he was the ace
at the Kangseng District Prosecutors' Office.

00:36:57.772 --> 00:36:59.538
He'd never failed to solve a case.

00:36:59.538 --> 00:37:02.238
Especially violent crimes.

00:37:02.238 --> 00:37:04.265
- And then?
- A suspect being questioned

00:37:04.265 --> 00:37:06.072
in the Hwang Kang Ae case killed himself.

00:37:06.072 --> 00:37:08.472
And he wasn't even the real culprit.

00:37:09.572 --> 00:37:11.772
So who's the ace now?

00:37:11.772 --> 00:37:13.572
Prosecutor Cha Si Young.

00:37:17.738 --> 00:37:19.038
Why do you ask?

00:37:19.038 --> 00:37:21.672
Trying to get close to prosecutors?

00:37:25.538 --> 00:37:27.238
You know,

00:37:28.172 --> 00:37:31.523
I'm about to lay out a really great spread.

00:37:32.305 --> 00:37:34.672
But I don't like the guy holding the spoon.

00:37:34.672 --> 00:37:36.272
It takes all the fun out of it.

00:37:36.272 --> 00:37:39.272
Then give it to someone else.

00:37:51.105 --> 00:37:53.238
What's with that man?

00:37:53.238 --> 00:37:54.238
He creeps me out.

00:37:54.238 --> 00:37:56.672
I know, he's weird.

00:37:57.505 --> 00:37:58.972
Go home. It's late.

00:38:01.172 --> 00:38:03.472
What? Did the lights go out?

00:38:03.472 --> 00:38:05.238
Seems like it's broken. I'm scared.

00:38:05.238 --> 00:38:08.572
I'll make sure
you get home safe, so hurry up.

00:38:08.572 --> 00:38:09.572
Really?

00:38:09.572 --> 00:38:11.872
Yeah, go on.

00:38:11.872 --> 00:38:13.905
I'm going.

00:38:13.905 --> 00:38:16.672
Bye, see you tomorrow!

00:38:43.438 --> 00:38:45.905
What? Hmph.

00:38:45.905 --> 00:38:48.238
You said you'd wait until I got home.

00:38:48.238 --> 00:38:50.638
That's low, Yu Jeong Rin.

00:39:06.872 --> 00:39:09.638
What should we eat after this?
Gopchang? Rice soup?

00:39:09.638 --> 00:39:10.672
Neither sounds good.

00:39:10.672 --> 00:39:13.305
Or should we just eat jjajangmyeon?

00:39:13.305 --> 00:39:14.505
I'm not feeling jjajangmyeon.

00:39:14.505 --> 00:39:15.538
Let's go have sweet and sour pork.

00:39:15.538 --> 00:39:17.472
- No, not that either.
- What do you think?

00:39:18.305 --> 00:39:20.838
I don't know.

00:39:20.838 --> 00:39:21.972
He's coming out.

00:39:21.972 --> 00:39:25.238
[New Era, New Police]

00:39:25.238 --> 00:39:29.505
Alright, step aside please.

00:39:31.638 --> 00:39:33.372
Get in.

00:39:36.738 --> 00:39:40.538
[Public Complaints Service Center]

00:39:42.105 --> 00:39:45.938
Let's go eat jokbal.

00:39:50.505 --> 00:39:51.605
Aren't you going to
the crime scene reenactment?

00:39:51.605 --> 00:39:53.672
I've got somewhere to be.

00:39:55.238 --> 00:39:57.172
You stay too, as you have work to do.

00:39:57.172 --> 00:39:58.872
Me?

00:39:59.705 --> 00:40:02.638
They've just headed to the scene.

00:40:02.638 --> 00:40:05.638
Departure was delayed by news reporters.

00:40:05.638 --> 00:40:06.972
A lot of reporters showed up?

00:40:06.972 --> 00:40:10.172
Yeah, looks like all the local papers
in Kangseng showed up.

00:40:10.172 --> 00:40:11.972
Do I look okay today?

00:40:11.972 --> 00:40:16.405
You're always at your best, sir.

00:40:16.405 --> 00:40:18.638
Officer,

00:40:18.638 --> 00:40:20.738
you've got a real eye for detail.

00:40:23.505 --> 00:40:26.572
Hey, look who's here.

00:40:26.572 --> 00:40:28.338
Came to see me?

00:40:30.138 --> 00:40:33.272
We're not exactly happy to see each other.

00:40:35.505 --> 00:40:38.538
So, how did you
get Lee Seong Jin's confession?

00:40:38.538 --> 00:40:40.638
Come on, that hurts.

00:40:40.638 --> 00:40:42.505
So you're more curious about him than me?

00:40:42.505 --> 00:40:44.238
Did you beat him?

00:40:44.972 --> 00:40:46.905
Or threaten him?

00:40:47.838 --> 00:40:50.472
You're good at that.

00:40:50.472 --> 00:40:54.305
If that's how you did it,
fix it yourself right now.

00:40:54.305 --> 00:40:56.538
Don't pin this on an innocent man.

00:40:58.672 --> 00:41:01.172
I've got something to say too.

00:41:03.172 --> 00:41:05.672
Yeah? What is it?

00:41:08.905 --> 00:41:10.938
Just say you're sorry.

00:41:10.938 --> 00:41:11.972
It's just that...

00:41:11.972 --> 00:41:13.572
Just one word.

00:41:13.572 --> 00:41:16.272
I heard you got kicked out of Seoul.

00:41:17.205 --> 00:41:19.172
So stop that and come with me.

00:41:19.172 --> 00:41:22.172
It's better to catch one murderer
than ten small-time crooks.

00:41:22.172 --> 00:41:24.672
Just come and pretend
to go through the reenactment.

00:41:24.672 --> 00:41:27.405
I'll put your name on the report.

00:41:27.405 --> 00:41:28.617
Well,

00:41:29.257 --> 00:41:32.772
I don't stick my nose
into other people's business.

00:41:32.772 --> 00:41:36.305
Especially when there's nothing
worth getting involved in.

00:41:48.038 --> 00:41:49.705
What are you even talking about?

00:41:49.705 --> 00:41:52.705
I'm telling you Lee Seong Jin
is not the real killer.

00:41:52.705 --> 00:41:54.605
Why are you telling me this?

00:41:54.605 --> 00:41:57.405
Lee Seong Jin isn't
even a suspect in my case...

00:41:57.405 --> 00:41:59.938
It's related to your case too, sir.

00:41:59.938 --> 00:42:02.005
Choi Min Ja, Hwang Kang Ae,

00:42:02.005 --> 00:42:06.438
and Im Bok Hee were
all killed by the same person.

00:42:06.438 --> 00:42:08.205
Do you have any evidence?

00:42:08.205 --> 00:42:10.305
No, not yet.

00:42:13.872 --> 00:42:16.072
What exactly do you want from me?

00:42:16.072 --> 00:42:18.872
The crimes all target women
returning home after sunset,

00:42:18.872 --> 00:42:21.172
sexual assault,
binding with victims' clothing,

00:42:21.172 --> 00:42:23.372
and then strangulation!

00:42:23.372 --> 00:42:28.105
What are the chances there are three killers
with the same method in Kangseng?

00:42:31.505 --> 00:42:35.938
Let's say, as you claim,
all of this is committed by a serial killer.

00:42:35.938 --> 00:42:36.969
Then,

00:42:36.969 --> 00:42:39.838
couldn't Lee Seong Jin still be the killer?

00:42:39.838 --> 00:42:41.105
Sir.

00:42:41.105 --> 00:42:45.865
Lee Seong Jin was in detention
at the time Hwang Kang Ae was killed.

00:42:48.105 --> 00:42:50.705
We'll find evidence soon.

00:42:50.705 --> 00:42:53.805
The more they kill,
the more addicted they become.

00:42:53.805 --> 00:42:56.005
This punk is going to kill again soon.

00:42:56.005 --> 00:42:57.738
Possibly...

00:43:01.572 --> 00:43:03.938
Yes, Prosecutor Hwang Jae Hoon's office.

00:43:05.705 --> 00:43:07.072
As early as today.

00:43:07.072 --> 00:43:09.705
Pardon? Who?

00:43:10.572 --> 00:43:13.905
Someone is looking for you,
Detective Kang Tae Joo.

00:43:17.038 --> 00:43:18.272
Sir!

00:43:18.272 --> 00:43:20.238
A body has been found.

00:43:20.238 --> 00:43:22.672
It's a murder case.

00:43:22.672 --> 00:43:24.372
Okay, I'll be right there.

00:43:29.238 --> 00:43:30.972
Evidence has appeared.

00:43:33.481 --> 00:43:35.305
Hold it!

00:43:36.265 --> 00:43:38.185
I said hold it.

00:43:39.593 --> 00:43:42.953
You touched her? You put your hands
all over the person like that?

00:43:42.953 --> 00:43:45.438
That's all you've got?

00:43:47.238 --> 00:43:51.272
I don't stick my nose
into other people's business.

00:43:51.272 --> 00:43:54.972
Especially when there's nothing
worth getting involved in.

00:43:54.972 --> 00:43:57.472
"Nothing worth getting involved in?"

00:44:10.851 --> 00:44:12.649
[Police]

00:44:12.649 --> 00:44:13.705
Jeez.

00:44:13.705 --> 00:44:15.438
What is it?

00:44:16.172 --> 00:44:17.905
- Hey! Stop!
- Stop him.

00:44:17.905 --> 00:44:20.105
Stop, stop, freeze!

00:44:20.105 --> 00:44:23.172
Freeze! Stop it...

00:44:23.172 --> 00:44:25.105
What are you doing right now?

00:44:25.105 --> 00:44:27.138
The reporters are all here!

00:44:28.038 --> 00:44:30.105
Well, another body was found.

00:44:30.105 --> 00:44:31.529
What does that have to do with this?

00:44:31.529 --> 00:44:33.972
- Another body?
- Another one's been found?

00:44:33.972 --> 00:44:35.705
- Don't tell me...
- Yes.

00:44:36.772 --> 00:44:38.238
Is it true another body has been found?

00:44:38.238 --> 00:44:41.038
What about the reenactment?

00:44:41.038 --> 00:44:44.238
Sir, is there really another body?

00:44:44.238 --> 00:44:46.938
Sir!

00:44:58.838 --> 00:45:00.238
Aren't you going to secure the scene?

00:45:00.238 --> 00:45:01.538
Secure the scene. Now.

00:45:01.538 --> 00:45:03.405
- Step out.
- Wait, but...

00:45:46.372 --> 00:45:48.572
[Yu Jeong Rin]
You were right, sir.

00:45:48.572 --> 00:45:50.405
It's the same guy.

00:45:55.572 --> 00:45:59.072
[You, the Hollyhock]

00:46:13.972 --> 00:46:18.438
So the same killer murdered
Yu Jeong Rin and Im Bok Hee?

00:46:18.438 --> 00:46:22.772
Yes, the method matches Im Bok Hee's case.

00:46:22.772 --> 00:46:26.205
We arrested a guy who wasn't the real killer
and even did a reenactment.

00:46:26.205 --> 00:46:28.305
Jeez, if it had gone to trial...

00:46:28.305 --> 00:46:30.138
Oh my.

00:46:30.138 --> 00:46:31.772
I'm ashamed.

00:46:31.772 --> 00:46:34.705
So what are you going to do now?

00:46:35.337 --> 00:46:38.025
Since it's definitely the same killer,

00:46:38.025 --> 00:46:40.505
we'll indict it together
with Yu Jeong Rin's case...

00:46:41.638 --> 00:46:43.405
Come in.

00:46:48.038 --> 00:46:50.238
Come sit.

00:46:54.338 --> 00:46:58.272
Mr. Hwang thinks differently from you.

00:46:59.138 --> 00:47:03.538
It's not two serial murder victims, but four.

00:47:03.538 --> 00:47:06.805
The first victim was Choi Min Ja.

00:47:10.472 --> 00:47:13.372
Don't you think that's a bit of a stretch?

00:47:13.372 --> 00:47:17.305
Choi Min Ja and Hwang Kang Ae
were killed in completely different ways.

00:47:17.305 --> 00:47:18.638
It can't be the same killer.

00:47:18.638 --> 00:47:20.072
What's different?

00:47:20.072 --> 00:47:22.405
Weekdays, after sunset,

00:47:22.405 --> 00:47:24.305
crimes targeting women returning home.

00:47:24.305 --> 00:47:26.772
And strangulation.

00:47:26.772 --> 00:47:31.472
But Im Bok Hee was strangled with stockings.

00:47:31.472 --> 00:47:34.538
The killer develops preferences over time.

00:47:34.538 --> 00:47:37.405
He used to use
any of the victim's belongings,

00:47:37.405 --> 00:47:39.538
but has now become fixated on stockings.

00:47:39.538 --> 00:47:42.072
He found that, due to the elasticity,

00:47:42.072 --> 00:47:45.005
stockings lead to a slower death
than other materials.

00:47:46.038 --> 00:47:48.672
So the goal is a slow death?

00:47:48.672 --> 00:47:50.138
Not the texture of it?

00:47:50.138 --> 00:47:51.593
That way,

00:47:52.201 --> 00:47:54.705
he can prolong the pleasure.

00:47:54.705 --> 00:47:56.572
The pleasure of killing.

00:47:58.505 --> 00:48:02.705
The next crimes will surely involve
strangulation with stockings.

00:48:02.705 --> 00:48:04.538
I'm certain of it.

00:48:09.072 --> 00:48:13.472
In any case, you still don't have
direct evidence, do you?

00:48:13.472 --> 00:48:15.838
I'll continue my investigation my own way.

00:48:15.838 --> 00:48:18.105
Mr. Cha, have you forgotten already?

00:48:18.105 --> 00:48:20.505
That you almost wronged an innocent person?

00:48:23.872 --> 00:48:25.605
Give me one more chance.

00:48:25.605 --> 00:48:28.538
I'm confident this time.

00:48:38.872 --> 00:48:40.572
This case...

00:48:42.569 --> 00:48:45.905
Excuse me for a second.

00:49:21.838 --> 00:49:24.005
Tae Joo

00:49:25.772 --> 00:49:28.138
is still so adorable.

00:49:31.938 --> 00:49:33.772
What should I do about you?

00:49:51.205 --> 00:49:53.772
[You, the Hollyhock]

00:49:53.772 --> 00:49:55.472
This book

00:49:56.538 --> 00:49:59.005
was found next to Jeong Rin.

00:50:00.005 --> 00:50:02.938
The guy from the bookstore gave it to her.

00:50:03.938 --> 00:50:05.972
That mark...

00:50:06.872 --> 00:50:10.038
That was because of Jeong Rin.

00:50:16.472 --> 00:50:18.705
Which bookstore?

00:50:18.705 --> 00:50:21.072
Kangseng Bookstore.

00:50:22.238 --> 00:50:24.905
That handsome guy there.

00:50:26.672 --> 00:50:30.105
Were you on your way home
after stopping by there?

00:50:32.472 --> 00:50:34.172
Yes.

00:50:40.372 --> 00:50:43.672
Anyone suspicious on the way?

00:50:53.805 --> 00:50:55.538
Wait...

00:50:56.872 --> 00:50:59.572
I think I know

00:50:59.572 --> 00:51:02.272
who killed Jeong Rin.

00:51:03.972 --> 00:51:06.172
Who is it?

00:51:08.772 --> 00:51:12.138
Min Ji, over there...

00:51:12.138 --> 00:51:14.472
Stop right there! I'll catch you!

00:51:19.005 --> 00:51:20.705
Shh.

00:51:23.785 --> 00:51:25.641
What's going on?

00:51:37.538 --> 00:51:40.938
Did you see a woman come this way?

00:51:41.705 --> 00:51:43.625
I think she went this way.

00:51:43.625 --> 00:51:45.385
Darn it!

00:51:48.338 --> 00:51:52.138
Hey, what if you get caught lying?

00:51:52.138 --> 00:51:53.481
It's okay.

00:51:53.481 --> 00:51:55.205
Let's hurry.

00:52:01.638 --> 00:52:08.105
[Specialized Hand Washing for All Shoes]

00:52:08.738 --> 00:52:09.738
Hello.

00:52:09.738 --> 00:52:11.738
Ms. Kim, you're here.

00:52:15.205 --> 00:52:16.738
Nothing special.

00:52:16.738 --> 00:52:18.638
No criminal record, either.

00:52:19.472 --> 00:52:20.872
One thing suspicious though,

00:52:20.872 --> 00:52:24.672
he's been closing the laundry shop
early for months now.

00:52:26.638 --> 00:52:29.105
He must be very busy.

00:52:29.105 --> 00:52:31.438
Hope today's no different.

00:52:35.972 --> 00:52:40.205
[Eun Ho Automatic Laundry]

00:52:40.205 --> 00:52:42.205
Duck.

00:53:12.538 --> 00:53:14.838
- Shall we go?
- Let's go.

00:53:37.538 --> 00:53:39.205
You won't learn until you get hit.

00:53:39.205 --> 00:53:40.705
Stop it, don't!

00:53:40.705 --> 00:53:41.805
You punk!

00:53:41.805 --> 00:53:43.938
Police, are you okay?

00:53:43.938 --> 00:53:45.405
Stay still, you punk!

00:53:45.405 --> 00:53:46.605
Kim Han Seop!

00:53:46.605 --> 00:53:47.705
Stay still, you punk!

00:53:47.705 --> 00:53:49.905
- Let go of me!
- Stay still.

00:53:49.905 --> 00:53:51.772
Stay still, Kim Han Seop, you'll get hurt.

00:53:51.772 --> 00:53:52.772
Who are you?

00:53:52.772 --> 00:53:55.538
- I said let go!
- Stay still.

00:53:56.738 --> 00:53:59.905
That woman is my wife.

00:53:59.905 --> 00:54:02.872
Is it a crime to bring back my runaway wife?

00:54:09.372 --> 00:54:11.238
You remember these students?

00:54:11.238 --> 00:54:13.972
Three days ago, Dugang-ri underpass.

00:54:13.972 --> 00:54:15.705
So?

00:54:16.638 --> 00:54:21.005
This one was murdered
right after they ran into you.

00:54:21.005 --> 00:54:22.738
What?

00:54:23.905 --> 00:54:26.372
It wasn't me! Why would I?

00:54:26.372 --> 00:54:29.572
At first, I thought it was a coincidence too.

00:54:29.572 --> 00:54:34.272
Until I saw you were about
to stab people with scissors.

00:54:34.272 --> 00:54:37.005
I was just trying to scare her.

00:54:37.005 --> 00:54:40.438
If I meant to kill her,
I would've brought a knife.

00:54:40.438 --> 00:54:41.438
A knife?

00:54:41.438 --> 00:54:42.568
I mean,

00:54:42.568 --> 00:54:45.972
a knife would be easier to use.

00:54:47.971 --> 00:54:49.193
Jeez.

00:54:55.738 --> 00:54:57.705
This guy isn't the killer.

00:54:58.638 --> 00:55:00.372
Here.

00:55:00.372 --> 00:55:02.872
Go ahead.

00:55:02.872 --> 00:55:04.705
Thank you.

00:55:04.705 --> 00:55:07.205
I ran away from him.

00:55:07.205 --> 00:55:10.172
He used to beat me almost every day.

00:55:10.172 --> 00:55:14.438
After that, he seemed to be
looking for me every night.

00:55:16.705 --> 00:55:20.205
On the 19th around 8 PM,

00:55:20.205 --> 00:55:23.072
you ran into these students, right?

00:55:25.538 --> 00:55:27.238
Yes.

00:55:28.772 --> 00:55:33.005
How long were you
hiding from Kim Han Seop then?

00:55:33.005 --> 00:55:37.038
About an hour, I think.

00:55:37.038 --> 00:55:40.605
I was there for quite a while,
worried he might come back.

00:55:41.472 --> 00:55:45.772
Did Kim Han Seop come back that way again?

00:55:45.772 --> 00:55:47.472
No.

00:55:48.405 --> 00:55:51.305
Then, anyone who passed by on that road?

00:55:52.738 --> 00:55:56.472
No people, though.

00:55:56.472 --> 00:55:58.705
"No people?"

00:55:58.705 --> 00:56:02.005
Did you notice anything suspicious?

00:56:02.005 --> 00:56:05.872
Anything you can remember.

00:56:05.872 --> 00:56:07.465
Well,

00:56:07.465 --> 00:56:10.172
I'm not entirely sure, but...

00:56:11.505 --> 00:56:13.438
Shh.

00:56:13.438 --> 00:56:16.638
I'm certain I saw a scarecrow.

00:56:27.805 --> 00:56:30.638
But later, it was gone.

00:56:33.705 --> 00:56:36.009
A scarecrow...

00:56:36.009 --> 00:56:39.205
There was a scarecrow, and...

00:56:40.872 --> 00:56:43.882
And I think I heard

00:56:43.882 --> 00:56:46.138
stray dogs too.

00:56:47.372 --> 00:56:49.305
Where was that?

00:56:59.472 --> 00:57:01.172
Hey!

00:57:03.405 --> 00:57:05.438
What? It's just a scarecrow.

00:57:05.438 --> 00:57:07.172
You startled me.

00:57:13.605 --> 00:57:15.338
Min Ji.

00:58:45.438 --> 00:58:47.938
Did you see a woman come this way?

00:58:47.938 --> 00:58:50.072
I think she went this way.

00:58:50.738 --> 00:58:52.472
That day,

00:58:54.172 --> 00:58:57.072
the reason the stray dogs
were wary of the scarecrow,

00:58:58.438 --> 00:59:03.038
and the reason the victims

00:59:03.038 --> 00:59:05.272
weren't wary of him.

00:59:30.872 --> 00:59:33.338
Look at this punk.

00:59:33.338 --> 00:59:36.205
This guy's completely out of his mind.

00:59:37.605 --> 00:59:40.105
You've walked right into my hands now.

01:00:17.205 --> 01:00:19.305
You better hide well.

01:00:20.038 --> 01:00:22.638
And watch your back.

01:00:23.972 --> 01:00:25.872
I'm going to catch you.

01:00:45.538 --> 01:00:47.272
Who's there?

01:00:58.272 --> 01:01:00.005
Who is it?

01:01:05.772 --> 01:01:07.505
Tae Joo?

01:01:09.905 --> 01:01:11.805
It is you, Tae Joo.

01:01:14.538 --> 01:01:15.977
Well,

01:01:15.977 --> 01:01:17.205
why are you here?

01:01:17.205 --> 01:01:19.505
I went to check the Yu Jeong Rin case.

01:01:19.505 --> 01:01:22.372
I thought it might be you.

01:01:22.372 --> 01:01:24.338
Put that thing away.

01:01:24.338 --> 01:01:25.872
Why are you acting so scary?

01:01:25.872 --> 01:01:28.038
So why are you here?

01:01:28.038 --> 01:01:31.205
This isn't even your case anymore.

01:01:31.205 --> 01:01:32.713
Exactly.

01:01:32.713 --> 01:01:35.005
It's not my case anymore.

01:01:35.005 --> 01:01:37.572
I heard you took over this case?

01:01:37.572 --> 01:01:41.505
If you wanted it, you could've just told me.

01:01:41.505 --> 01:01:45.538
Then we could've solved it
together as friends. Isn't it great?

01:01:45.538 --> 01:01:48.805
If you dare say 'us' or 'friends'
in front of me again,

01:01:48.805 --> 01:01:51.005
I'll kill you with my own hands!

01:01:51.005 --> 01:01:52.838
Don't mess with me!

01:01:52.838 --> 01:01:55.972
I'm not the old Kang Tae Joo anymore!

01:01:55.972 --> 01:02:00.172
That guy was patient and naive, but I'm not!

01:02:08.372 --> 01:02:10.538
Stay out of my sight as much as possible.

01:02:10.538 --> 01:02:12.605
It won't take long.

01:02:12.605 --> 01:02:15.172
I don't plan on staying here long anyway.

01:02:18.305 --> 01:02:20.172
Kang Tae Joo!

01:02:24.605 --> 01:02:27.205
I'll take this case back.

01:02:29.905 --> 01:02:31.638
And you too.

01:02:33.005 --> 01:02:34.072
What?

01:02:34.072 --> 01:02:35.273
I will

01:02:35.273 --> 01:02:37.805
keep you by my side.

01:02:37.805 --> 01:02:39.538
Like back then.

01:02:42.405 --> 01:02:44.238
You psycho!

01:02:44.872 --> 01:02:48.338
I missed you, Kang Tae Joo.

01:02:56.305 --> 01:02:58.505
- You punk!
- Hey, hey!

01:02:58.505 --> 01:03:00.272
Hold on, hold on.

01:03:04.438 --> 01:03:06.405
- This way.
- Okay.

01:03:10.115 --> 01:03:13.138
[If you have a dream,
you can always start over]

01:03:13.138 --> 01:03:15.945
I've waited for this day

01:03:15.945 --> 01:03:18.505
for a long time.

01:03:19.905 --> 01:03:22.238
For the past 30 years.

01:03:23.538 --> 01:03:25.505
Hold on.

01:03:25.505 --> 01:03:27.072
Yes?

01:03:27.072 --> 01:03:29.072
Do you have water?

01:03:29.072 --> 01:03:32.038
Yes, it's ready. Let's go.

01:03:37.315 --> 01:03:40.579
[Strong rule of law,
humane and effective corrections]

01:03:40.579 --> 01:03:46.211
[It is about striving
to live a righteous life]

01:04:26.838 --> 01:04:28.672
You're late.

01:04:32.505 --> 01:04:34.238
Have you been

01:04:35.438 --> 01:04:37.572
waiting long?

01:04:44.272 --> 01:04:46.072
Yes.

01:04:47.772 --> 01:04:49.905
Finally, we meet.

01:04:51.372 --> 01:04:53.705
The murderer I've been searching for

01:04:55.605 --> 01:04:57.572
all this time.

01:05:30.705 --> 01:05:33.305
Please help me!

01:05:33.305 --> 01:05:35.238
It felt soft... like a woman's hand.

01:05:35.238 --> 01:05:37.605
If you see anything suspicious
like a scarecrow, run away immediately.

01:05:37.605 --> 01:05:39.338
It might be the killer.

01:05:40.672 --> 01:05:42.338
Detective Kang, I'm the prosecutor

01:05:42.338 --> 01:05:44.605
before I'm your friend.

01:05:44.605 --> 01:05:47.705
If it's a weakness, we can find another one.

01:05:49.438 --> 01:05:52.838
Hey, your sister is in the hospital.

01:05:53.938 --> 01:05:58.472
After what happened to his sister,
what kind of brother wouldn't lose it?